question: Show me the total cost for all invoices for the district.
text: Here is the total cost for all invoices in your district.
sql_used: SELECT SUM(i.total_cost) AS total_cost FROM invoices i WHERE i.district_key = :district_key;

question: Show me the total cost of invoices by month.
text: Here is the total cost of invoices grouped by service month for your district.
sql_used: SELECT i.service_month, SUM(i.total_cost) AS total_cost FROM invoices i WHERE i.district_key = :district_key GROUP BY i.service_month ORDER BY i.service_month;

question: Show me the year-to-date total cost of invoices.
text: Here is the year-to-date total cost of invoices for your district.
sql_used: SELECT SUM(i.total_cost) AS total_cost FROM invoices i WHERE i.district_key = :district_key AND strftime('%Y', i.invoice_date) = strftime('%Y', 'now');

question: Show me total invoice cost broken down by vendor.
text: Here is the total invoice cost broken down by vendor for your district.
sql_used: SELECT v.name AS vendor_name, SUM(i.total_cost) AS total_cost FROM invoices i JOIN vendors v ON v.id = i.vendor_id WHERE i.district_key = :district_key GROUP BY v.name ORDER BY total_cost DESC;

question: Show me each student's total expenses.

question: How much do we pay for LVNs?

question: How many providers support Jack Garcia by month? Show me the names.
text: Here are the providers supporting Jack Garcia by service month, including counts and names.
sql_used: SELECT service_month, COUNT(clinician) AS provider_count, GROUP_CONCAT(clinician, ', ') AS providers FROM ( SELECT DISTINCT i.service_month AS service_month, c.full_name AS clinician FROM invoice_line_items ili JOIN invoices i ON i.id = ili.invoice_id JOIN clinicians c ON LOWER(c.full_name) = LOWER(ili.clinician) WHERE i.district_key = :district_key AND LOWER(ili.student) = LOWER('Jack Garcia') ) GROUP BY service_month ORDER BY service_month;

question: Give me a summary of how many students are serviced by each vendor.
text: Here is a summary of how many distinct students are serviced by each vendor.
sql_used: SELECT v.name AS vendor_name, COUNT(DISTINCT ili.student) AS student_count FROM invoice_line_items ili JOIN invoices i ON i.id = ili.invoice_id JOIN vendors v ON v.id = i.vendor_id WHERE i.district_key = :district_key GROUP BY v.name ORDER BY student_count DESC;

question: Give me a summary of what each vendor does for our students.
text: Here is a summary of vendor services, including the number of students and total cost per vendor.
sql_used: SELECT v.name AS vendor_name, COUNT(DISTINCT ili.student) AS student_count, SUM(ili.cost) AS total_cost FROM invoice_line_items ili JOIN invoices i ON i.id = ili.invoice_id JOIN vendors v ON v.id = i.vendor_id WHERE i.district_key = :district_key GROUP BY v.name ORDER BY total_cost DESC;

question: Tell me which providers deliver care for each student.
text: Here is a mapping of students to the providers who deliver their care.
